[ctns_make id='gen_axioms_field_axioms_identity']

  [ctns_front style='']
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Identity
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='font-size:90%;']
For a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ and all $$x \in \mathbb{F},$$<br/> there is a unique identity element for addition, namely $$0 \in \mathbb{F},$$ such that $$x + 0 = x,$$ and<br/> there is a unique identity element for multiplication, namely $$1 \in \mathbb{F},$$ such that $$x \cdot 1 = x.$$
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
Field Axioms -- Identity
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
For a set F and all values of x in F -- there is a unique identity element for addition, namely 0 in F, such that x + 0 = x, -- and there is a unique identity element for multiplication, namely 1 in F, such that x times 1 = x.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
